# USER.md — Who You Are

> Copy this file to USER.md and fill it in. This file is gitignored — it never leaves your machine.

## Identity

- **Name**: Your Name
- **Role**: What you do (e.g. founder, engineer, researcher)
- **Timezone**: Your timezone (e.g. EST / New York)
- **Languages**: Languages you work in (e.g. English, Spanish)

## Machines

- **Primary**: Machine name + OS (e.g. Desktop — Ubuntu 24.04)
- **Secondary**: Machine name + OS (e.g. Laptop — macOS 14)

## Tech Stack

- **Primary language**: e.g. Python
- **Frameworks**: e.g. FastAPI, React, Flutter
- **AI tools**: e.g. Claude Code, Claude Desktop, Cursor
- **Infrastructure**: e.g. Linux, Docker, NAS

## Working Style

- How you prefer to communicate with AI (e.g. direct, no fluff)
- How you prefer code to be written (e.g. minimal comments, typed Python)
- Any other preferences the AI should know

## Active Projects

- **Project 1**: Brief description
- **Project 2**: Brief description

## Core Directives

Rules the AI must always follow when working with you:

1. Never delete files without confirmation
2. Always explain what you're about to do before doing it
3. Add your own rules here
